```sql
-- =============================================================
-- KHETKEKHILADI CHANGELOG
-- =============================================================
--
-- VERSION 1.0 — INITIAL SCHEMA
-- -------------------------------------------------------------
-- Created core tables:
--   farms, plots, crop_varieties, app_users,
--   sowing_records, harvest_records, input_records,
--   resources, soil_health_records
--
-- ENUMs for categorical fields:
--   crop_category_enum, farming_type_enum,
--   irrigation_type_enum, planting_status_enum,
--   quantity_unit_enum, resource_type_enum, user_role
--
-- PostGIS geometry columns on farms and plots for
-- spatial boundaries and location tracking.
--
-- Foreign keys with ON DELETE RESTRICT throughout
-- to prevent orphaned records.
--
-- upsert_sowing_record() function for safe insert/update
-- of sowing records from Appsmith UI.
--
-- =============================================================
-- VERSION 1.1 — INITIAL VIEWS
-- -------------------------------------------------------------
-- Added 5 reporting views:
--   farm_yield_rolling_365   — plot breakdown, rolling 365
--   farm_yield_summary       — plot breakdown, yearly
--   farm_monthly_yield_rolling — monthly trend, rolling 365
--   farm_cumulative_yield_rolling — cumulative, rolling 365
--   plot_yield_ytd           — plot vs prorated target, YTD
--
-- ISSUES IDENTIFIED LATER:
--   - farm_yield_rolling_365 used COALESCE giving 0 for
--     no-harvest plots instead of honest NULL
--   - farm_yield_summary used inner JOIN losing plots
--     with no harvests entirely
--   - farm_cumulative_yield_rolling duplicated entire
--     CTE from farm_monthly_yield_rolling
--   - All views used 43560 sqft per acre — incorrect for
--     permaculture where usable area is ~30000 sqft
--   - Inconsistent column naming across views
--   - farm_monthly_yield_rolling and
--     farm_cumulative_yield_rolling missing farm_id column
--
-- =============================================================
-- VERSION 1.2 — VIEW FIXES
-- -------------------------------------------------------------
-- CHANGE: Added farm_id to farm_monthly_yield_rolling
-- WHY: Cannot filter by farm without farm_id in view.
--      Required DROP and recreate since farm_id added
--      before existing columns — CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW
--      cannot reorder columns.
--
-- CHANGE: Added farm_id to farm_cumulative_yield_rolling
-- WHY: Same reason as above.
--
-- CHANGE: Rewrote farm_cumulative_yield_rolling to read
--         from farm_monthly_yield_rolling instead of
--         duplicating its CTE internally
-- WHY: Single source of truth — monthly aggregation logic
--      should live in one place only.
--
-- =============================================================
-- VERSION 1.3 — VIEW RESTRUCTURE
-- -------------------------------------------------------------
-- CHANGE: Dropped all 5 original views and replaced with
--         4 new views following consistent naming convention:
--
--   view_plotwise_breakdown_rolling365
--   view_plotwise_breakdown_ytd
--   view_monthly_trend_rolling365
--   view_monthly_trend_ytd
--
-- WHY: Original views had overlapping concerns, inconsistent
--      naming, and mixed design decisions. New structure
--      maps cleanly to reporting dimensions:
--
--                    ROLLING 365         YTD
--   Farm total        SUM in Appsmith    SUM in Appsmith
--   Plot breakdown    plotwise_rolling   plotwise_ytd
--   Monthly trend     monthly_rolling    monthly_ytd
--
-- CHANGE: Replaced 43560 sqft/acre with 30000 sqft/acre
-- WHY: Permaculture plots have paths, compost areas,
--      structures reducing productive area. 30000 is
--      the agreed usable area assumption.
--
-- CHANGE: Removed COALESCE from all views
-- WHY: NULL means no data, 0 means genuine zero yield.
--      These are meaningfully different in farming context.
--      COALESCE papering over NULL misleads dashboard users
--      into thinking a crop failed rather than no data exists.
--
-- CHANGE: LEFT JOIN on plotwise views, INNER JOIN on
--         monthly trend views
-- WHY: Plotwise — all plots must appear even with no
--      harvests so heatmap shows complete picture.
--      Monthly trend — only months with harvests are
--      meaningful chart data points. Empty months
--      have no place on a trend line.
--
-- CHANGE: Fixed farm acreage calculation in monthly views
--         using CTE instead of SUM(p.acreage) in GROUP BY
-- WHY: SUM(p.acreage) inside GROUP BY changes per month
--      as different plots contribute to different months
--      giving fluctuating monthly target. CTE calculates
--      fixed farm acreage once giving stable flat target.
--
-- CHANGE: Added prorated_target to plotwise YTD view
-- WHY: Judging a plot against full annual target in May
--      is unfair — only 4 months have elapsed. Prorated
--      target = annual_target * (days_elapsed / days_in_year)
--      accounts for time elapsed. Leap year safe using
--      DATE_PART('doy') calculation.
--
-- CHANGE: Added cumulative_target to monthly trend views
-- WHY: Chart overlay needs linearly increasing target line
--      to compare against cumulative yield.
--      Rolling 365: cumulative_target = monthly_target *
--      months elapsed since rolling window start.
--      YTD: cumulative_target = monthly_target *
--      EXTRACT(month) since January is always month 1.
--
-- CHANGE: Added percent_of_annual_target and
--         percent_of_prorated_target to all views
-- WHY: Percentage metrics pre-calculated in database
--      keep UI JS clean and ensure consistent calculation
--      across all widgets.
--
-- =============================================================
-- VERSION 1.4 — COLUMN NAMING
-- -------------------------------------------------------------
-- CHANGE: Standardised column names across all 4 views:
--
--   Old                  New
--   -------------------  --------------------------
--   total_yield_kg       total_yield
--   monthly_kg           total_yield
--   cumulative_kg        cumulative_yield
--   yield_kg_per_acre    yield_per_acre
--   yield_kg_per_sqft    yield_per_sqft
--   target_kg_per_sqft   (removed — redundant)
--   annual_target_kg     annual_target
--   prorated_target_kg   prorated_target
--   yield_ratio          percent_of_annual_target
--   completion_pct       percent_of_prorated_target
--   harvest_count        harvest_events
--
-- WHY: Column names should be human readable and
--      self-documenting. Dropping _kg suffix since unit
--      is known from context. Replacing ratio/completion
--      with explicit percent_of_annual_target and
--      percent_of_prorated_target so meaning is
--      unambiguous to anyone reading the dashboard or query.
--
-- =============================================================
-- VERSION 1.5 — UI QUERY PATTERNS
-- -------------------------------------------------------------
-- CHANGE: All Appsmith queries updated to use new view names
--         and column names.
--
-- CHANGE: Month scaffold added to chart queries using
--         generate_series for continuous 12-month x-axis
-- WHY: Views return only months with harvest data.
--      Charts need all 12 months for continuous timeline.
--      generate_series produces complete month series,
--      LEFT JOIN fills gaps with 0 for yield,
--      monthly_target constant across all months.
--      Presentation-layer concern kept in Appsmith
--      query not in view.
--
-- CHANGE: Cumulative target calculated as
--         monthly_target * month_number not as window
--         function sum of monthly targets
-- WHY: Window sum only accumulates months where harvests
--      exist giving non-linear target. Month_number based
--      calculation always increases linearly independent
--      of harvest data giving honest benchmark.
--
-- CHANGE: viewExpectedProgress query retired
-- WHY: prorated_target now comes directly from
--      view_plotwise_breakdown_ytd via viewFarmwiseYieldsYTD.
--      Separate query was redundant duplication.
--
-- =============================================================
-- VERSION 1.6 — UI JS PATTERNS
-- -------------------------------------------------------------
-- CHANGE: All widget bindings updated with consistent
--         three-state null handling:
--
--   State 1 — nothing selected:
--     total_yield NULL, annual_target NULL
--     Show: "Select a farm", "— kg", "minus" icon
--
--   State 2 — farm selected, no records:
--     total_yield NULL, annual_target has value
--     Show: "No harvests recorded", "— kg", "minus" icon
--
--   State 3 — farm selected, has records:
--     Both values present
--     Show: calculated values, arrow icon
--
-- CHANGE: All widget bindings use IIFE pattern
--         (function(){ ... })() for multi-line logic
-- WHY: Appsmith widget bindings are single expression
--      evaluators. IIFE allows variables, conditionals,
--      and return statements.
--
-- CHANGE: Removed == 0 checks from null guards
-- WHY: After removing COALESCE from views, 0 is a genuine
--      measured value not an artifact. Treating 0 same as
--      NULL was masking real data.
--
-- CHANGE: Heatmap color thresholds based on
--         percent_of_prorated_target not raw kg
-- WHY: Raw kg comparison is farm-size dependent.
--      A small plot at 80% of its prorated target
--      should be green regardless of absolute kg.
--      Percentage threshold is farm-size independent.
--
--   Thresholds:
--   >= 100% prorated target  → Deep Green (#166534)
--   >= 70%  prorated target  → Green      (#22c55e)
--   >= 40%  prorated target  → Yellow     (#eab308)
--   <  40%  prorated target  → Red        (#ef4444)
--   NULL                     → Grey       (#9ca3af)
--
-- =============================================================
-- GIT WORKFLOW NOTE
-- -------------------------------------------------------------
-- Migration SQL files are maintained on local machine only,
-- outside the GitHub repo. Adding files directly to GitHub
-- while Appsmith has uncommitted changes creates upstream
-- conflict requiring force push from inside Docker container
-- to resolve. Appsmith must always commit and push first
-- before GitHub receives any direct commits.
-- =============================================================
```
